or and defensor ideologies did not begin in the fifteenth century, but rather had a much older origin, and it is suggested that the conflict continued after 1500. Textual sources include the Siete partidas, wills, chronicles, religious works such as the Arte de bien morir and literary works such as Cárcel de Amor and Celestina.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aDeathxHistoryy15th centuryzSpainzCastile. 0aDeathxReligious aspects. 0aDeathxSocial aspectszSpainzCastile. 0aDeathzSpainzCastilexHistoryy15th century. 0aFuneral rites and ceremoniesxHistoryy15th centuryzSpainzCastile. 0aFuneral rites and ceremonieszSpainzCastilexHistoryy15th century. 0aMourning customsxHistoryy15th centuryzSpainzCastile. 0aMourning customszSpainzCastilexHistoryy15th century. 4aHispanic Studies. 4aMedieval History. 4aMedieval Literature. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Death & Dying.2bisacsh  aCastile.  aSpanish ecclesiastics.  aSpanish history.  aSpanish nobility.  afifteenth century.  amedieval Christianity.  amedieval Spain.  amedieval aristocracy.  amedieval attitudes towards death.  amedieval death rituals.  amedieval funeral rites.  amedieval ideology.  amedieval literature.  amedieval social classes.  amedieval texts.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package pre 2013z978311143139040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781846150630423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781846150630/original  a978-3-11-143139-0  Boydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package pre 2013b2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles